I have tested Data Table component. Please evaluate the possibility to have two separate components: "SimpleTable" and "Table". Rename existing implementation to the "SimpleTable" and it will be available for both Web and Email. Implement new "Table" component based on React Aria's Table and make it available for the Web Frames only.
Make sure we will be able to render new React Aria's Table based component to all Web targets (React, Angular, Html)

Table Component:

- MJML has a real mj-table — it accepts plain <tr>/<th>/<td> HTML with inline styles (it's an "ending tag", no nested MJML). So a Data Table can export to email, making it a candidate
  second all-four-target component (after Divider) — provided cells stay plain.
- React Aria's Table is a heavyweight stateful collection component (Table/TableHeader/Column/TableBody/Row/Cell, selection/keyboard/drag) — powerful, but SSR-risky and divergent from the
  static markup the generators emit.

